description:
Creator of the raw and violent comic series 'Raw Deal' together with work mate H.P. McElwee who died of a heart attack in 1998 at the age of 43. The sixth issue was published after his death with material he'd already written.

Lawrence still owns the Real Deal website. It is unsure if there will be more issues. There was talk of issue #7 coming out in 2011/2012, but so far (aug, 2014) there's been no more word about it.
name: Lawrence Hubbard

deck: Milorad Pavić (1929-2009) was a Serbian writer and literary historian. His most famous novel was the Dictionary of the Khazars (1984), hailed as "the first novel of the 21st century." His works have been translated into more than thirty languages and he was a potential candidate for the Nobel Prize in Literature.
description: Several of Pavić's works have been adapted into comics and graphic novels, including "Third Argument" graphic novel by artist Zoran Tucić and writer Zoran Stefanović (1995), republished in three parts in Heavy Metal Magazine (1998-2000).
name: Milorad Pavic
